history.content:
Think of 61C as like the workload 61B but just spread out more evenly (smaller peaks). Math 110 and 113 aren't too bad. It's like 4-6 hours of work a week prob and the both are pretty straight forward. Think of 170 as the same workload as 70.

I guess it's doable but you will probably be very sad. Depends on how much work you want to do next semester and what you're used to.

Note: I took 61C over the summer and didn't think it was too bad but I hear that over the semester it's extremely time-consuming and most don't recommend taking it with other heavy classes

children.subject: I would say Math 113 is generally quite a bit harder than Math 110 due to the longer proofs you have to write and the newer concepts (the linear algebra concepts in 110 are often just a more rigorous presentation of those in 54)
I think there is an alternate final for 61c. You have to take back to back finals on friday night up till 1am though.
